Interface SequentialBatchResponse<T>

Sequential Batch Response

Complete response from sequential batch execution with tier-based pricing metadata.

Example

Response structure:
{
  results: [
    [signature1, signature2, ...],  // From getSignaturesForAddress
    [tx1, tx2, ...]                 // From getTransaction (expanded)
  ],
  metadata: {
    quotaCost: 20.21,              // 1 base + 19.21 expansion
    baseQuota: 1,
    expansionQuota: 19.21,
    totalExpansions: 24,
    tier: 'free',
    expansionRate: 0.80,
    executionTime: 1850.48,
    pairCount: 1,
    actualRpcCalls: 25,
    sequentialApplied: true,
    pairs: [...]
  }
}
interface SequentialBatchResponse<T> {
    errors?: {
        error: any;
        pairIndex: number;
        requestIndex: number;
    }[];
    metadata: {
        actualRpcCalls: number;
        baseQuota?: number;
        executionTime: number;
        expansionQuota?: number;
        expansionRate?: number;
        pairCount: number;
        pairs: {
            chainingApplied: boolean;
            executionTime: number;
            expanded: boolean;
            expandedCount?: number;
            methods: string[];
            pairIndex: number;
            quotaCost: number;
        }[];
        pricingModel?: "tier-based" | "flat";
        quotaCost: number;
        sequentialApplied: boolean;
        tier?: string;
        totalExpansions?: number;
    };
    results: T[];
}
